# Python Dojo

Intro Python learning app: lessons, practice, exam prep, capstones. Runs entirely in the browser (Pyodide).

## Stack

- Vite 8 · React 19 · TypeScript (strict) · React Router 7
- Zustand (progress store + localStorage persist)
- Zod (content schemas)
- Pyodide (in-browser Python), CodeMirror (editors)
- Vitest (unit) · Playwright (e2e)

## Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `npm run dev` | Dev server (port 5173) |
| `npm run build` | Production build |
| `npm run test` | Unit tests |
| `npm run test:e2e` | Playwright smoke tests |
| `npm run lint` | ESLint (src/ only) |
| `npm run validate-content` | Zod-validate all lessons & capstones |

## Workflow

- Commit after each verified feature set; run `build`, `test`, and `validate-content` before committing.
- Keep business logic in `src/engine/`, not in components.
- Add lesson content under `src/content/lessons/`; validate with `npm run validate-content`.
- Do not edit files under `reference/` — third-party clones for inspiration only.
- UI uses the “command center” HUD theme; page titles live in `HudHeader.tsx` (`Command Overview`, `Review Session`, `Telemetry Log`, etc.).

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase (`ExampleCard.tsx`)
- Engine/store/utils: camelCase files (`practiceQueue.ts`)
- Lesson IDs: `lesson01` … `lesson16`
- Example IDs: `{lesson}-c{n}-e{n}` pattern
